      "Bash(git commit -m \"$\\(cat <<''EOF''\nEliteMobs 10.0.0 SNAPSHOT\n\nMajor update introducing the comprehensive Skill System, replacing the old Guild Rank system.\n\n[New] Complete Skill System overhaul!\n  - Six weapon skill categories: Swords, Axes, Bows, Crossbows, Tridents, and Hoes\n  - Armor skill category for defensive abilities\n  - Each category has 7-11 unique skill bonuses players can unlock\n  - Skills are earned through combat XP with the corresponding weapon/armor type\n  - Progressive skill unlock system with increasing XP requirements per level\n\n[New] 70+ unique skill bonuses across all weapon categories:\n  - Swords: Blade Dance, Duelist, Expose Weakness, Finishing Flourish, Flurry, Lacerate, Parry, Poise, Riposte, Swift Strikes, Vorpal Strike\n  - Axes: Devastating Blow, Executioner, Momentum, Reckless Fury, Stagger, Timber, Wound\n  - Bows: Barrage, Dead Eye, Frostbite, Hunter''s Mark, Multishot, Overdraw, Pack Hunter, Ranger''s Focus, Ricochet, Wind Runner\n  - Crossbows: Arrow Rain, Explosive Tip, First Blood, Heavy Bolts, Hunter''s Prey, Quick Reload, Steady Aim, Suppressing Fire\n  - Tridents: Depth Charge, Impale, Leviathan Wrath, Poseidon''s Favor, Returning Haste, Riptide Mastery, Snare, Storm Caller, Tidal Surge, Undertow\n  - Hoes \\(Scythes\\): Death Mark, Death''s Embrace, Dread Aura, Grim Reach, Harvester, Reap What You Sow, Reaper''s Harvest, Scythe Sweep, Soul Drain, Soul Siphon, Spectral Scythe\n  - Armor: Adrenaline Surge, Battle Hardened, Evasion, Fortify, Grit, Iron Stance, Last Stand, Reactive Shielding, Retaliation, Second Wind\n\n[New] Skill bonus types with different activation mechanics:\n  - Proc skills: Chance-based activation on hit/damage\n  - Cooldown skills: Powerful effects with cooldown timers\n  - Stacking skills: Build up stacks for increasing power\n  - Toggle skills: Manual activation/deactivation\n  - Conditional skills: Activate when specific conditions are met\n\n[New] Combat Level system!\n  - Player combat level calculated from all skill levels combined\n  - Combat Level Display shows player''s power above their head\n  - XP bars show progress toward next skill level\n  - Skills Page in status screen shows all skill progress\n\n[New] Skill Bonus Menu!\n  - Interactive GUI for selecting active skill bonuses\n  - Shows unlocked vs locked skills\n  - Displays skill descriptions and effects\n  - Configurable via SkillBonusMenuConfig\n\n[New] Training Dummies!\n  - Five training dummy bosses at levels 1, 25, 50, 75, and 100\n  - Practice combat and test skill bonuses\n  - No loot or XP - purely for training\n\n[New] Skill testing framework!\n  - /em skilltest command for combat simulations\n  - /em skilltest cancel to stop tests\n  - CombatSimulator for automated DPS testing\n  - Detailed test reports with damage breakdowns\n\n[New] Farming Protection system!\n  - Prevents cheese strategies like suffocation traps\n  - Configurable protection thresholds\n  - Ensures fair combat engagement\n\n[New] Gear Restriction Handler!\n  - Items can require minimum skill levels to use effectively\n  - Enforces progression requirements\n\n[New] Commands for skill management:\n  - /em skillcheck <player> - View player''s skill levels\n  - /em skillset <player> <skill> <level> - Set specific skill level\n  - /em skillsetall <player> <level> - Set all skills to level\n\n[Removed] Old Guild Rank system completely removed:\n  - GuildRank.java deleted\n  - GuildRankMenuHandler.java deleted\n  - GuildRankMenuConfig.java deleted\n  - WorldSwitchBehavior.java deleted\n  - GuildRankCommands.java deleted\n  - RankCommand.java deleted\n  - RankSetCommand.java deleted\n\n[Tweak] Updated to Java 21\n[Tweak] Updated EasyMinecraftGoals to 1.19.22\n[Tweak] Simplified shadowJar relocate configuration\n[Tweak] AdventurersGuildConfig significantly reduced after Guild Rank removal\n[Tweak] Combat system enhanced with skill bonus integration\n[Tweak] Damage events now track skill bonus applications\n\n[Fix] Translation system now properly handles camelCase language names \\(e.g., chineseSimplified\\)\n[Fix] Language code lookup now uses lowercase comparison while preserving original filename case\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code]\\(https://claude.com/claude-code\\)\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n\\)\")",
